conclusion: CYP2C19*2 homozygous — Poor metabolizer. Dramatically reduced clopidogrel activation; increased cardiovascular event risk. Consider prasugrel or ticagrelor. Also affects PPI and SSRI metabolism.
CYP2C19*2 heterozygous — Intermediate metabolizer. Reduced clopidogrel efficacy; consider alternative antiplatelet therapy. Moderate reduction in PPI and SSRI metabolism.
CYP2C19 normal function at this locus. Standard clopidogrel response expected.
CYP2C19*3 homozygous — Poor metabolizer. Complete loss of CYP2C19 function. Same clinical implications as *2 homozygous.
CYP2C19*3 heterozygous — Intermediate metabolizer. One non-functional allele. Reduced drug activation.
CYP2C19 normal function at *3 locus.
CYP2C19*17 homozygous — Ultra-rapid metabolizer. ~2x increased transcription. May cause subtherapeutic levels of PPIs and SSRIs. Enhanced clopidogrel activation (potentially increased bleeding risk).
CYP2C19*17 heterozygous — Rapid metabolizer. Moderately increased enzyme activity. Clinical significance depends on co-occurring *2/*3 alleles (diplotype).
CYP2C19 normal transcription rate at *17 locus.

CYP2D6*4 homozygous — Poor metabolizer. No functional CYP2D6 enzyme. Codeine ineffective (no morphine conversion). Tamoxifen ineffective (no endoxifen). Increased adverse effects from tricyclic antidepressants.
CYP2D6*4 heterozygous — Intermediate metabolizer. Reduced but not absent enzyme activity. May need dose adjustments for CYP2D6 substrates.
CYP2D6 normal function at *4 locus. Standard metabolism of codeine, tamoxifen, and psychiatric medications.
CYP2C9*2 homozygous — Reduced function. Approximately 20% lower warfarin dose required. Increased bleeding risk at standard doses. Also affects NSAID and phenytoin metabolism.
CYP2C9*2 heterozygous — Mildly reduced function. ~10% warfarin dose reduction may be needed. Monitor INR closely during initiation.
CYP2C9 normal function at *2 locus. Standard warfarin metabolism.
CYP2C9*3 homozygous — Severely reduced function. ~50% lower warfarin dose required. Highest bleeding risk genotype. Mandatory dose adjustment for warfarin and phenytoin.
CYP2C9*3 heterozygous — Moderately reduced function. ~25% lower warfarin dose. Clinically significant; include in pharmacogenomic dosing algorithms.
CYP2C9 normal function at *3 locus. Standard warfarin metabolism.
CYP3A4*22 homozygous — Reduced expression. Significantly lower CYP3A4 activity. Lower statin doses needed; higher tacrolimus/cyclosporine trough levels. Monitor closely.
CYP3A4*22 heterozygous — Moderately reduced expression. May benefit from lower statin starting dose. Monitor immunosuppressant levels.
CYP3A4 normal expression. Standard metabolism of statins and immunosuppressants.
